  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0ba9\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0b95\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A request to all political parties",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Honorable President Gotabaya Rajapaksa made very important promises in his final speech before the nation.",
        "His recent failure to deliver on his promises has now come to light. By submitting the 22nd Constitutional Amendment Bill, he has clarified the difference between the amendment process expected by the government and the political amendment claimed by the civil society and political parties of the country.",
        "Because of that, the National Movement for Social Justice insists on the immediate fulfillment of the promises made by the President who delivered a special speech in front of the people on May 11, 2022.",
        "Similarly, we would like to inform you that we cannot trust the 22nd constitutional amendment in comparison with the difference between the government's position and the people's expectations.",
        "Following this, as an organization working in the interest of the country, we emphasize that we are not ready to give up our expectations regarding the political, economic and social reforms that should really be carried out in Sri Lanka.",
        "Similarly, we request all the political party leaders and civil society organizations in the country to come together to re-enforce the basic principles contained in the 19th Amendment.",
        "We also consider the need to provide an immediate solution to the massive political and economic crises in the country.",
        "For that, we are warning the political forces that if the country is not directed towards possible political reforms, the worst situations may occur in the country.",
        "We also emphasize that if the political parties representing the government and the parliament and their leaders fail in this duty, the situation may be worse than the normal situation the country is currently facing.",
        "Therefore, all the political parties and members of the people representing the Parliament should try to provide solutions to the current economic crisis and work to create a multi-party government in order to win the trust of the people both domestically and abroad.",
        "At the same time, while expressing our agreement with the recommendations given by the Most Venerable Mahanayaka Theras on two occasions, he also requested us to consider the recommendations put forward by the Sri Lankan Bar Association and civil societies."
      ],
